DAMATURU – The peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Yobe state chapter has confirmed the nomination of Mohammed M. Bukar alias Terro as Tarmuwa, Gulani Damaturu and Gujba candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) for the forthcoming 2023 general elections. This was contained in a press statement signed by the PDP State Publicity Secretary (Yobe), Salihu Mohammed Baba. According to him, the emergence of Mohammed M. Bukar as the House of Representatives candidate followed the substitution of Abdullahi Idris who earlier won the primary election and later withdrew from the race. “The substitution was made based on the mandate of the party constitution where both of them unanimously agreed to work together to ensure the victory of the party in the forthcoming 2023 elections”. The event for the Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) took place in presence of Yobe state PDP zonal working committee members in Damaturu, Yobe State capital.